No in all reality this isn’t Aurora at all but air glow and light pollution from Banff captured on my Astro modified camera. In lady Aurora’s defense the data was pretty weak when I was up there. Either way I’ve got the bug and I’m ready to chase a big CME.

Painted Pillows- those who know me as a photographer know that I have a moderate obsession with foregrounds. I love flowers and wood but snow pillows oh how I love snow pillows. On a recent trip to #banffnationalpark I immediately spotted these pillows off the beaten path. After traversing down we found another photographer shooting above. Being considerate I stayed out of his shot but lamented out loud how epic these pillows would be as an FG. 

Being a kind Canadian he was like no problem and let me shoot them. Most Americans would have given me the middle finger 😂. Needless to say the resulting exposure might be an all time favorite.

This is STEVE. He paid me a visit in WY on Thursday night during a strong Geomagnetic Storm. STEVE stands for Strong Thermal Emission Velocity Enhancement and while it’s not rare it’s still pretty new to science (discovered in 2015). This was my first time seeing the #auroraborealis and it was life changing. I know this shot is a departure from my normal style but some things are so beautiful they don’t need a foreground.

Winter Warmer- getting great pictures takes a lot of work both in the field and in post processing. The difference of seconds can mean missing great light or capturing colorful clouds. So although our cameras and our accessories are just tools I’m always looking at refining my kit to improve my work flow.

For the last couple years I had worked with screw on and square filter sets. They have been great but they are cumbersome to carry and to be honest excruciatingly slow to set up. When @kasefilterglobal approached me about a collaboration to work with the KW Revolution Magnetic Filter set I was excited to try out a product that was smaller and significantly reduced setup time. Here’s a shot I took with the Kase Circular Polarizer. Let me know what you think!
